Step 5: Build CRNN model with CTC loss
max_label_length = 20   # choose based on expected word length
crnn_model = build_crnn_model(cnn_model, rnn_model, max_label_length)
crnn_model.summary()

Step 6: Train the CRNN model

(You will need: labels, label_lengths, input_lengths)

crnn_model.compile(optimizer="adam")
crnn_model.fit(x=train_images, y=None, epochs=50)

Step 7: Predict
inference_model = build_inference_model(cnn_model, rnn_model)
preds = inference_model.predict(test_img)
decoded_text = ctc_decode(preds, char_list)
print(decoded_text)